Right now the code to get the license file from the nupkg one has to do roughly the following:
* Obtain an instance of `PackageArchiveReader`;
* Create an instance of `NuspecReader` using the return value of `PackageArchiveReader.GetNuspec`;
* Get the `LicenseMetadata` from `NuspecReader`;
* Check if `LicenseType` is `File`;
* Get the value of `LicenseMetadata.License` and "fix" the path by calling `PathUtility.StripLeadingDirectorySeparators`;
* Call the `PackageArchiveReader.GetEntry()` passing the value obtained in the previous step (or get missing file exception if path contains backslashes or starts with `.`.);
* Finally, call the `Open` on the `ZipArchiveEntry` instance to get the contents.

That seems like a quite complicated process, involving at least one non-obvious step (calling the `PathUtility.StripLeadingDirectorySeparator` to transform path to zip-friendly form), that either needs to be very clearly documented, or deserves its own method in `PackageArchiveReader` (might be overkill to add it here) or `NuspecReader` (`GetLicenseFileName`?).

Another issue is that this `PathUtility.StripLeadingDirectorySeparator` call looks optional and it's easy not to call it and it will work for a basic case of having the file at the root of the zip archive, which, I would guess, would be the majority of cases. And then it will break on paths with backslashes.
